Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.78,0:00:19.23,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Ta-da!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.33,0:00:22.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you dressed like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.30,0:00:24.08,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Vacation! Vacation!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.21,0:00:26.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Why "vacation"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.07,0:00:28.24,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.23,0:00:32.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Did you not tell the Vice Commander yet, Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.52,0:00:33.78,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.78,0:00:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told her there'd be no Orgone energy \Nmovement for the next three days...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.34,0:00:39.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,So we're going on vacation!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.47,0:00:43.23,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you always going to the pool \Nand eating sweets on the job?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.46,0:00:46.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Those aren't vacations... Those are breaks!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.71,0:00:50.00,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, it's been nothing but hard missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:53.84,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,And sleeping in a train car every \Nnight makes my shoulders stiff...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.84,0:00:57.20,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand the situation we're in?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.57,0:00:59.02,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.46,0:01:03.18,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what tomorrow will bring,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.18,0:01:04.83,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,so we need to take a vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.42,0:01:07.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.63,0:01:14.17,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if we were normal students, \Nwe'd be on summer break now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.73,0:01:17.33,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But given what's going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.57,0:01:25.02,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,True, you guys may need a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.59,0:01:27.00,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.00,0:01:30.06,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give the Midsummer's Knights \Npermission for a vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.38,0:01:32.74,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Us, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.19,0:01:36.99,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But make sure we can reach \Nyou at any time, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.99,0:01:39.06,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Pitz, she says we're going on vacation!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.90,0:01:41.29,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.26,0:03:15.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're ready to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.36,0:03:17.80,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,You fixed them, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:19.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.74,0:03:21.34,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That was faster than planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.67,0:03:23.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.76,0:03:25.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget to give us that data!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.11,0:03:29.85,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who said
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.85,0:03:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should leave the Machine Goodfellow \Ntesting to Amara and Moco, Puck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.79,0:03:39.36,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,But the development schedule \Nis lagging badly behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.77,0:03:42.25,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,The pilot's mental state
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.25,0:03:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,greatly affects the Neural Maneuver \NSystem's capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.38,0:03:50.58,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,The method we're using is the best \Nway to obtain the data we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.01,0:03:53.97,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,When humanity goes to space \Nfor the Kivotos Plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.97,0:03:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that system will be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.66,0:04:00.80,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,Is it falling behind because they're slacking,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.80,0:04:03.44,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,or because they're uncooperative?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.44,0:04:06.93,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I have no data on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.25,0:04:09.04,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,We must do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.62,0:04:13.54,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,Is there some system that would allow us
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.54,0:04:16.40,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,to control people more directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.81,0:04:24.24,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you're the only one at the \Ncompany I can truly control...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.55,0:04:30.16,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget that I have your \Nemergency shutdown switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.80,0:04:33.51,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Puck does not lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.49,0:04:37.54,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the Machine Goodfellows are fixed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.56,0:04:42.88,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,...we don't have Setsuna's capsule anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:50.84,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,The new engine series is \Nfinally nearing completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.84,0:04:53.33,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be great to have a spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.63,0:04:56.10,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Once this new model is complete,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.10,0:04:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this and the Nebula Engine will be a great help.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.01,0:05:03.45,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,But in the scenario you have in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.45,0:05:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this will do more than simply enhance \Nthe intercept system, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.04,0:05:12.08,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What did Alonzo say about that plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:14.48,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,They're still running the numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.48,0:05:16.47,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Give them a little more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.07,0:05:31.40,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez... For the first time in ages, \Nwe get to sleep in big beds!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.40,0:05:34.29,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, just remember to exercise restraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.50,0:05:49.11,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the room next to mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.92,0:06:00.83,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I have this huge room to myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.64,0:06:18.79,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.24,0:06:23.73,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The rooms are connected? No, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.76,0:06:27.70,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They're the same room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.70,0:06:31.57,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This is just one room with two entrances!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.57,0:06:34.08,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I think they're called connecting rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.38,0:06:36.70,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,C-Connecting rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.60,0:06:39.42,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Connecting rooms!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.44,0:06:43.66,Default - italics,D,0000,0000,0000,,You set us up, didn't you, Akari?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.14,0:06:45.96,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all sweaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.96,0:06:46.76,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.16,0:06:48.74,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking a bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.13,0:06:54.22,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,A bath...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.36,0:07:00.73,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.61,0:07:04.94,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.41,0:07:25.38,Title,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1781,1)\an3}A Maiden's Tear That Sparkled \NThrough the Night
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.90,0:07:31.02,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,"Hey, Akari... This isn't funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.02,0:07:34.24,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hana and me in the same room? \NYou can't do that!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.13,0:07:38.60,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I was expecting him to come \Nand say that, but I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:42.29,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What do you do on vacation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:44.36,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.09,0:07:46.57,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.88,0:07:48.05,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Goodnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.05,0:07:49.98,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,G-Goodnight...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.05,0:08:50.34,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.09,0:08:52.49,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.09,0:09:16.20,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.55,0:09:52.65,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, how did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.35,0:09:54.90,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,How did what go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.64,0:09:57.87,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I showed restraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.87,0:09:59.58,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Restraint?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.58,0:10:01.10,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, restraint...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.10,0:10:02.79,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I exercised perfect restraint!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.96,0:10:05.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.90,0:10:07.44,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.20,0:10:09.48,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.48,0:10:11.78,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Are you talking about last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.78,0:10:13.05,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.35,0:10:16.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,"Not a thing," he says...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.32,0:10:17.40,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.85,0:10:19.30,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,"Why"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.62,0:10:21.22,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:24.63,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,but I think she might hate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.63,0:10:26.56,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hate you? Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.56,0:10:28.26,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,She hates you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:36.82,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, have you ever considered modeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.37,0:10:39.26,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,No photographs!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.26,0:10:40.55,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Just one...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.40,0:10:42.72,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me, Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.72,0:10:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.56,0:10:45.08,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Of course she doesn't hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:49.18,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,When you go to sleep before she does,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.84,0:10:53.30,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,she often goes over to kiss you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.07,0:11:17.07,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.72,0:11:20.08,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You want to get some ice cream?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.08,0:11:21.11,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.78,0:11:23.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like ice cream?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.09,0:11:25.36,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.42,0:11:29.33,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Do you prefer mint chocolate chip or vanilla?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.75,0:11:32.89,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I like both of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.89,0:11:35.75,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess mint chocolate chip?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:37.84,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Then, mint chocolate chip or the captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.20,0:11:39.21,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.61,0:11:41.53,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I thought so...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.93,0:11:55.20,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.83,0:11:58.98,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,They're still underage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.94,0:12:08.04,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps I overestimated you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.04,0:12:13.57,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,Another complaint came in from \NTechnology and Research Division 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.39,0:12:19.09,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,You took out some Machine Goodfellows \Nwithout permission, and got them destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.71,0:12:25.01,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,And you also used the Orgone \Nenergy capsules, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.36,0:12:27.78,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,Those are a valuable energy resource.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.78,0:12:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A single one can power the latest \Nmobile weaponry for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.33,0:12:33.69,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,What did you use them for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.93,0:12:38.22,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,What do you have to do to \Ndrain a capsule completely?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.22,0:12:40.73,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,The two of us fought a mock battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.73,0:12:42.96,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It was part of our pilot training.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.96,0:12:47.59,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We thought improving our skills \Nwould benefit the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.59,0:12:48.28,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,You're wasting time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.43,0:12:51.45,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,The Neural Maneuver Systems need
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.45,0:12:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to be tailored to a specific \Nindividual, or it's pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.25,0:12:57.75,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,The Machine Goodfellows are not your toys!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.57,0:13:02.87,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, you are forbidden \Nto use them without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.87,0:13:06.22,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,And you must obey Technology \Nand Research Division 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:08.41,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.99,0:13:12.36,Default,Ku,0000,0000,0000,,Don't disappoint me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.60,0:13:22.23,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, Malkin-sama... Amarok-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.72,0:13:25.98,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think we need Masaki Kube anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.98,0:13:27.30,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,He's obnoxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.30,0:13:32.24,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I estimate that we need \NMasaki Kube a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:37.71,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Eliminating him will make controlling \NMacbeth Enterprises more difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.11,0:13:40.70,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,When a man who's only lived a few decades
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.70,0:13:42.41,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,treats me like a little kid,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.41,0:13:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it irritates my real self more than anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.62,0:13:48.76,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Masaki Kube can still be useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.21,0:13:54.43,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,The Globe Tanegashima base's Independent \NAttack Force is a bigger problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.22,0:14:00.20,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,They've stopped every attempt at an \Nabreaction via Machine Goodfellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.67,0:14:02.57,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.07,0:14:04.44,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.44,0:14:06.32,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.43,0:14:20.46,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The satellite, Legacy, was made by the \NSeton Company as part of Kube's plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:23.94,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The stock satellite Kube built \Nfor the escape into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.94,0:14:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's halfway between the Earth and Moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.87,0:14:30.93,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather not waste food...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.66,0:14:34.49,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But if we dropped the Legacy on Tanegashima...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.80,0:14:42.56,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,It'd blow the island away, \Nand cause problems for Kube.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.17,0:14:45.09,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Two birds with one stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.83,0:14:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.93,0:14:49.99,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it, can't you, Puck?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.03,0:14:52.99,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.54,0:15:06.29,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know that there's a \Ntotal lunar eclipse tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.04,0:15:10.47,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I worked so hard to arrange a \Nromantic setting for them...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.09,0:15:14.29,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I guess they're still kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.74,0:15:18.45,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Hana was born of my race...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.55,0:15:22.38,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,So I think she has the same nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.38,0:15:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same peculiarity, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.74,0:15:28.54,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,When we kiss someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.54,0:15:33.31,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,we can feel what they're thinking, to an extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.31,0:15:35.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,A kind of telepathy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.41,0:15:36.42,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.78,0:15:38.50,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A telepathic kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.45,0:15:41.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Telepathic kiss?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.74,0:15:47.42,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that I could see what she \Nwas thinking then, for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.75,0:15:56.35,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, doesn't Hana only \Nkiss the captain when he's asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.45,0:16:01.05,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,If Hana does have that peculiarity...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.04,0:16:32.34,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.72,0:16:41.64,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:46.11,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I should just kill you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.12,0:16:50.39,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.19,0:16:54.69,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I love you, Daichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.77,0:17:09.79,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I want to kiss you, Hana.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.45,0:17:14.69,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.65,0:17:16.89,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.98,0:17:22.22,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,If you knew my real self...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.22,0:17:25.44,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You'd hate me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.35,0:17:34.82,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,An emergency call?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.15,0:17:37.02,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? This is Manatsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.02,0:17:38.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:41.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Midsummer's Knights, get here now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.75,0:17:48.58,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! It's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.99,0:17:50.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.24,0:17:54.26,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The Seton Company's modified asteroid, Legacy,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in halo orbit around L1, has fired its engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.96,0:17:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's starting to accelerate toward Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.59,0:18:10.48,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a little over a dozen hours \Nsince Legacy went out of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.89,0:18:12.68,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,It's less than a hundred meters in diameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.68,0:18:14.41,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Something that small can't be detected
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.41,0:18:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by the space guard's early warning system!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.52,0:18:21.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Legacy will crash into Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.16,0:18:25.50,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Legacy sighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.92,0:18:28.75,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Verifying predicted point of impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:29.75,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:32.80,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The south end of Japan... Tanegashima!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.80,0:18:33.71,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.04,0:18:36.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Less than 420 seconds to impact!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.20,0:18:40.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Legacy satellite weighs around 100,000 tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:45.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If it crashes, the energy output \Nwill be in the megatons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.36,0:18:49.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This base... No, all of \NTanegashima will be destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.35,0:18:51.90,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is this an attack by them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.43,0:18:54.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Legacy is our stock satellite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.65,0:18:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's where we've kept the materials \Nneeded for the Kivotos Plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.72,0:19:01.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Who's behind this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.51,0:19:05.81,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,The Legacy appears to have been set \Non a course to strike Tanegashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.38,0:19:08.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're after the Globe base?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.65,0:19:10.21,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Likely, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.88,0:19:12.84,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.34,0:19:22.39,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No one can stop it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.37,0:19:24.72,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The low-orbit Impacters?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.29,0:19:26.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Citronnier is the closest!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.36,0:19:30.48,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be able to intercept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.96,0:19:36.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A 100,000-ton satellite is heading \Nstraight toward Tanegashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.32,0:19:37.71,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Can we intercept?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.71,0:19:40.63,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's already moving six kilometers per second...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.33,0:19:45.08,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,With that much kinetic energy, \Neven if we destroy it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:47.26,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,it won't change the damage it does!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.58,0:19:49.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.86,0:20:00.30,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the staff in the underground \Nblocks to stay there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.16,0:20:03.26,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is there no way to evacuate the civilians?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.42,0:20:05.51,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,150 seconds to impact!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.65,0:20:07.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.21,0:20:11.81,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.29,0:20:35.38,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.59,0:20:41.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm detecting a high-intensity heat source \Ncoming from the Tanegashima coast!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.23,0:20:47.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Blume{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.78,0:21:38.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Legacy satellite has been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.08,0:21:42.53,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Blume{\i0}'s beam weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.14,0:21:46.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Blume{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.00,0:21:48.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Did the {\i1}Blume{\i0} do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.39,0:21:52.12,Default,Am,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've done it, Princess...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.56,0:21:55.12,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.84,0:21:57.62,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That was the {\i1}Blume{\i0}'s Orgone beam.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.83,0:22:01.84,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Then Hana did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.90,0:22:22.97,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.26,0:22:29.78,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the girl you think I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.83,0:22:31.91,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.91,0:22:32.91,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.19,0:22:36.00,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.52,0:22:42.76,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.84,0:24:16.81,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Hana runs away from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.81,0:24:19.19,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,and by chance, finds Setsuna in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.19,0:24:23.46,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Amara and Moco from the \NPlanetary Gears find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.94,0:24:26.52,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Run, Hana! They're after you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.04,0:24:33.07,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Big changes are coming for Hana, \NSetsuna, and Macbeth Enterprises.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.07,0:24:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on episode 15 of {\i1}Captain Earth{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.28,0:24:38.04,Title2,,0000,0000,0000,,True Self
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.70,0:24:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True Self.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.04,0:24:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine, scramble!
